        "info": {
          "title": "NestleModel",
          "version": "lj4jk4akzolo3nnv",
          "description": "# Bentoml run \u0026 deploy\n\n## Local Model Execution\n\nTo run the model locally, execute the following commands:\n\n    conda env update -f conda.yaml -n bentoml\n    bentoml_import_model.py\n    bentoml_test.py just model, no service\n    bentoml serve .\n\n## OCI image creation:\n\n    python3 bentoml_import_model.py # imports the model  \n    bentoml build --containerize # builds container image\n\n## Local model execution trough docker\n    docker run --rm -p 3000:3000 \u003cimage_name\u003e # image name is provided in the last line of previous command output\n\n## To test the model, you can use the web interface or a curl request\n\n```bash\ncurl -X 'POST' \\\n  'http://localhost:3000/predict' \\\n  -H 'accept: application/json' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\n  \"input_data\": [\n    [1.53,40.76937484741211,-73.98515319824219,1,40.756778717041016,-73.97472381591797,0,2,0,1,11,22,16,59,0,1,11,22,26,28]\n  ]}'\n```\nWeb interface:  \n[http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)\n\n",
          "contact": {
            "name": "BentoML Team",
            "email": "contact@bentoml.com"
          }
        },
